Material Information Summary (Exploration Update):

  • Geophysical Survey Completed: Magnetotelluric (MT) survey at Colosseum Gold-REE Project (California) finished on 29 June 2025 (167 stations).
  • Key Findings:
  • High-resistivity anomaly identified (Line 2200N), coinciding with REE-bearing fenite dykes.
  • Geophysical signature resembles Mountain Pass REE deposit (gravity high, magnetic low, moderate resistivity: 70–120 Ω·m).
  • Geochemical Progress:
  • 916 of ~1,200 soil/rock samples collected (75% complete).
  • Initial assays confirm anomalous REE values (e.g., cerium, lanthanum) in surface samples.
  • Next Steps:
  • 3D MT inversion modeling (dual-team validation).
  • Final geochemical results and integrated target identification by mid-July.
  • Planned drilling campaign to test REE/gold targets (carbonatite intrusions and breccia pipes).

Existing Resource: 27.1Mt @ 1.26g/t Au (1.1Moz Au), 67% Measured & Indicated.

No capital raising, trading halt, or financial data disclosed.

Material Information Summary: Drilling Results at Fiesta Copper Project (Noronex Limited, ASX: NRX)

Key Highlights

  • Significant new intercepts from diamond drilling at Fiesta’s Western Lens:
  • 25FIEDD026:
    • 11m @ 0.5% Cu & 18g/t Ag from 371m
    • 6m @ 0.7% Cu & 15g/t Ag from 455m

  • Water bore (25FIEWB025) – potential contamination noted but intersects:

    • 9m @ 0.63% Cu & 21g/t Ag from 120m
    • 3m @ 1.0% Cu & 4g/t Ag from 137m

  • Program funded by South32 under an existing earn-in agreement (ref: ASX announcement 18 July 2024).

  • Two additional diamond holes planned, with assays pending for 25FIEDD027 and drilling ongoing at 25FIEDD028.

Geological Context

  • Mineralisation extends >4.5km strike length with vertical/sheeted structures.
  • Analogous to Khoemacau Copper Project (Botswana: 450Mt @ 1.4% Cu & 14g/t Ag).

Forward Work

  • Further drilling to test depth extensions and structural controls.

No material capital, financial, or timetable disclosures identified.

Focus: Expands resource potential; no immediate trading catalysts noted. Monitor assay updates.
